703
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:33,556
-Oh, come on. Tony. Tony.
-I'll be in the shop.

704
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:35,750
Hey, hey! Hey, Tony. Listen.

705
00:56:35,880 --> 00:56:39,031
I'm trying to turn this thing around,
but you gotta give me something.

706
00:56:39,160 --> 00:56:40,639
Something to pitch them.

707
00:56:40,760 --> 00:56:44,070
Let me have the engineers analyse that.
You know, draw up some specs.

708
00:56:44,200 --> 00:56:46,191
-No. No, absolutely not.
-It'll give me a bone to throw the boys

709
00:56:46,320 --> 00:56:47,799
-in New York!
-This one stays with me.

710
00:56:47,920 --> 00:56:50,593
-That's it, Obie. Forget it.
-All right, well, this stays with me, then.

711
00:56:50,720 --> 00:56:52,438
Go on, here, you can have a piece.

712
00:56:52,560 --> 00:56:53,959
-Take two.
-Thank you.

713
00:56:54,080 --> 00:56:55,832
You mind if I come down there
and see what you're doing?

714
00:56:55,960 --> 00:56:57,473
Good night, Obie.

715
00:56:58,120 --> 00:57:02,716
Day 1 1 , test 37, configuration 2.0.
For lack of a better option,

716
00:57:02,840 --> 00:57:05,354
Dummy is still on fire safety.
lf you douse me again,

717
00:57:05,480 --> 00:57:08,153
and I'm not on fire,
I'm donating you to a city college.

718
00:57:08,280 --> 00:57:09,998
<i>All right, nice and easy.</i>

719
00:57:10,120 --> 00:57:14,796
<i>Seriously, just gonna start off</i>
<i>with 1 % thrust capacity.</i>

720
00:57:16,280 --> 00:57:18,271
<i>And three, two, one.</i>

721
00:57:29,640 --> 00:57:30,595
Okay.

722
00:57:31,880 --> 00:57:33,393
Please don't follow me around
with it, either,

723
00:57:33,520 --> 00:57:35,795
'cause I feel like I'm gonna
catch on fire spontaneously.

724
00:57:35,920 --> 00:57:37,512
Just stand down!
lf something happens, then come in.

725
00:57:37,640 --> 00:57:39,756
And again, let's bring it up to 2.5.

726
00:57:39,880 --> 00:57:41,359
Three, two, one.

727
00:57:57,320 --> 00:57:59,754
Okay, this is where I don't want to be!

728
00:57:59,880 --> 00:58:01,108
Not the car, not the car!

729
00:58:02,440 --> 00:58:03,395
Table!

730
00:58:14,040 --> 00:58:17,953
Could be worse! Could be worse!
We're fine! Okay.

731
00:58:35,320 --> 00:58:36,753
No!

732
00:58:38,800 --> 00:58:40,358
Yeah, I can fly.

733
00:58:44,960 --> 00:58:47,758
-Jarvis, are you there?
<i>-At your service, sir.</i>

734
00:58:47,880 --> 00:58:49,996
-Engage Heads Up Display.
<i>-Check.</i>

735
00:58:50,120 --> 00:58:52,031
Import all preferences
from home interface.

736
00:58:52,160 --> 00:58:53,513
<i>Will do, sir.</i>

737
00:59:00,200 --> 00:59:01,155
All right, what do you say?

738
00:59:01,280 --> 00:59:01,600
<i>I have indeed been uploaded, sir.</i>
<i>We're online and ready.</i>

739
00:59:01,600 --> 00:59:04,558
<i>I have indeed been uploaded, sir.</i>
<i>We're online and ready.</i>

740
00:59:04,720 --> 00:59:06,233
Can we start the virtual walk-around?

741
00:59:06,360 --> 00:59:09,193
<i>lmporting preferences</i>
<i>and calibrating virtual environment.</i>

742
00:59:09,320 --> 00:59:10,514
Do a check on control surfaces.

743
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:12,073
<i>As you wish.</i>

744
00:59:33,080 --> 00:59:35,514
<i>Test complete. Preparing to</i>
<i>power down and begin diagnostics.</i>

745
00:59:35,640 --> 00:59:38,393
Yeah. Tell you what.
Do a weather and ATC check.

746
00:59:38,520 --> 00:59:39,919
Start listening in on ground control.

747
00:59:40,040 --> 00:59:41,029
<i>Sir, there are still terabytes</i>

748
00:59:41,160 --> 00:59:43,594
<i>of calculations needed</i>
<i>before an actual flight is...</i>

749
00:59:43,720 --> 00:59:47,429
Jarvis! Sometimes you got to run
before you can walk.

750
00:59:47,560 --> 00:59:51,633
Ready? ln three, two, one.

751
01:00:14,040 --> 01:00:15,712
Handles like a dream.

752
01:00:42,680 --> 01:00:44,193
All right, let's see what
this thing can do.

753
01:00:44,320 --> 01:00:45,639
What's SR-7 1's record?

754
01:00:45,760 --> 01:00:49,355
<i>The altitude record for fixed wing flight</i>
<i>is 85,000 feet, sir.</i>

755
01:00:49,800 --> 01:00:52,314
Records are made to be broken!
Come on!

756
01:00:55,400 --> 01:00:58,836
<i>Sir, there is a potentially fatal</i>
<i>buildup of ice occurring.</i>

757
01:00:58,960 --> 01:00:59,949
Keep going!

758
01:01:02,200 --> 01:01:03,428
Higher!

759
01:01:16,560 --> 01:01:20,633
We iced up, Jarvis!
Deploy flaps! Jarvis!

760
01:01:23,320 --> 01:01:25,515
Come on, we got to break the ice!

761
01:01:59,360 --> 01:02:00,554
Kill power.

762
01:03:21,360 --> 01:03:24,557
Notes. Main transducer feels sluggish
at plus 40 altitude.

763
01:03:24,680 --> 01:03:28,878
Hull pressurisation is problematic.
I'm thinking icing is the probable factor.

764
01:03:29,000 --> 01:03:31,116
<i>A very astute observation, sir.</i>

765
01:03:31,240 --> 01:03:32,878
<i>Perhaps, if you intend</i>
<i>to visit other planets,</i>

766
01:03:33,000 --> 01:03:34,353
<i>we should improve the exosystems.</i>

767
01:03:34,480 --> 01:03:36,914
Connect to the sys. co.
Have it reconfigure the shell metals.

768
01:03:37,040 --> 01:03:39,952
Use the gold titanium alloy from
the seraphim tactical satellite.

769
01:03:40,080 --> 01:03:43,755
That should ensure a fuselage integrity
while maintaining power-to-weight ratio.

770
01:03:43,880 --> 01:03:45,029
-Got it?
<i>-Yes.</i>

771
01:03:45,160 --> 01:03:47,355
<i>Shall I render</i>
<i>using proposed specifications?</i>

772
01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:48,708
Thrill me.

773
01:03:50,080 --> 01:03:54,437
<i>Tonight's red-hot red carpet is right</i>
<i>here at the Disney Concert Hall,</i>

774
01:03:54,560 --> 01:03:58,599
<i>where Tony Stark's third annual benefit</i>
<i>for the Firefighter's Family Fund</i>

775
01:03:58,720 --> 01:04:00,199
<i>has become the place to be</i>
<i>for L.A.'s high society.</i>

776
01:04:00,320 --> 01:04:01,469
Jarvis, we get an invite for that?

777
01:04:01,600 --> 01:04:03,955
<i>I have no record of an invitation, sir.</i>

778
01:04:04,080 --> 01:04:05,433
<i>...hasn't been seen in public</i>

779
01:04:05,560 --> 01:04:09,075
<i>since his bizarre and highly</i>
<i>controversial press conference.</i>

780
01:04:09,320 --> 01:04:11,834
<i>Some claim he's suffering</i>
<i>from posttraumatic stress</i>

781
01:04:11,960 --> 01:04:15,396
<i>and has been bedridden for weeks.</i>
<i>Whatever the case may be,</i>

782
01:04:15,880 --> 01:04:18,474
<i>no one expects an appearance</i>
<i>from him tonight.</i>

783
01:04:18,600 --> 01:04:20,636
<i>The render is complete.</i>

784
01:04:20,760 --> 01:04:22,318
A little ostentatious, don't you think?

785
01:04:22,440 --> 01:04:25,352
<i>What was I thinking?</i>
<i>You're usually so discreet.</i>

786
01:04:26,960 --> 01:04:29,428
TelI you what.
Throw a little hot-rod red in there.

787
01:04:29,560 --> 01:04:32,279
<i>Yes, that should help you</i>
<i>keep a low profile.</i>

788
01:04:35,360 --> 01:04:37,157
<i>The render is complete.</i>

789
01:04:37,640 --> 01:04:39,437
Hey, I like it. Fabricate it. Paint it.

790
01:04:39,560 --> 01:04:41,039
<i>Commencing automated assembly.</i>

791
01:04:41,160 --> 01:04:44,152
<i>Estimated completion time is five hours.</i>

792
01:04:44,280 --> 01:04:45,269
Don't wait up for me, honey.

793
01:05:08,560 --> 01:05:12,109
Weapons manufacturing is only
one small part of what Stark lndustries

794
01:05:12,240 --> 01:05:15,789
is all about, and our partnership
with the fire and rescue community...

795
01:05:18,360 --> 01:05:20,749
-Hey, Tony, remember me?
-Sure don't.

796
01:05:22,240 --> 01:05:23,639
You look great, Hef.

797
01:05:25,440 --> 01:05:26,668
We're going to have a great quarter.

798
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:30,349
What's the world coming to when
a guy's got to crash his own party?

799
01:05:30,480 --> 01:05:34,473
Look at you. Hey, what a surprise.

800
01:05:34,600 --> 01:05:36,238
I'll see you inside.

801
01:05:36,800 --> 01:05:39,917
Hey. Listen, take it slow, all right?

802
01:05:40,040 --> 01:05:41,678
I think I got the board
right where we want them.

803
01:05:41,800 --> 01:05:45,190
You got it. Just cabin fever.
I'll just be a minute.

804
01:05:49,560 --> 01:05:52,916
-Give me a Scotch. I'm starving.
-Mr Stark?

805
01:05:53,640 --> 01:05:55,278
-Yeah?
-Agent Coulson.

806
01:05:55,800 --> 01:05:57,870
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
The guy from the...

807
01:05:58,000 --> 01:06:01,151
Strategic Homeland lntervention,
Enforcement and Logistics Division.

808
01:06:01,280 --> 01:06:02,793
God, you need a new name for that.

809
01:06:02,920 --> 01:06:04,751
Yeah, I hear that a lot.

810
01:06:05,560 --> 01:06:09,189
Listen, I know this must be a trying time
for you, but we need to debrief you.

811
01:06:09,320 --> 01:06:11,151
There's still
a lot of unanswered questions,

812
01:06:11,280 --> 01:06:13,032
and time can be a factor
with these things.

813
01:06:13,160 --> 01:06:15,071
Let's just put something on the books.

814
01:06:15,200 --> 01:06:18,351
How about the 24th at 7:00 p.m.
at Stark lndustries?

815
01:06:18,760 --> 01:06:21,832
Tell you what.
You got it. You're absolutely right.

816
01:06:22,080 --> 01:06:26,119
Well, I'm going to go to my assistant,
and we'll make a date.

817
01:06:27,520 --> 01:06:29,476
You look fantastic!
I didn't recognise you.

818
01:06:29,600 --> 01:06:31,750
-What are you doing here?
-Just avoiding government agents.

819
01:06:31,880 --> 01:06:33,552
-Are you by yourself?
-Yes. Where'd you get that dress?

820
01:06:33,680 --> 01:06:35,398
-Oh, it was a birthday present.
-That's great.

821
01:06:35,520 --> 01:06:37,511
-From you, actually.
-Well, I got great taste.

822
01:06:37,640 --> 01:06:38,789
Yes.

823
01:06:38,920 --> 01:06:40,672
-You want to dance?
-Oh, no.

824
01:06:40,800 --> 01:06:43,189
-All right, come on.
-Thank you. No.

825
01:06:53,200 --> 01:06:55,316
Am I making you uncomfortable?

826
01:06:55,760 --> 01:07:00,754
No. No. I always forget to wear
deodorant and dance with my boss

827
01:07:00,880 --> 01:07:04,509
in front of everyone that I work with
in a dress with no back.

828
01:07:04,800 --> 01:07:07,234
-You look great and you smell great.
-Oh, God.

829
01:07:07,360 --> 01:07:09,112
But I could fire you if that would
take the edge off.

830
01:07:09,240 --> 01:07:12,676
I actually don't think that
you could tie your shoes without me.

831
01:07:12,800 --> 01:07:14,153
-I'd make it a week. Sure.
-Really?

832
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:16,635
What's your Social Security number?

833
01:07:20,000 --> 01:07:21,638
-Five.
-Five?

834
01:07:22,480 --> 01:07:23,708
-Right.
-Right.

835
01:07:23,840 --> 01:07:26,035
You're missing just
a couple of digits there.

836
01:07:26,160 --> 01:07:29,152
The other eight?
So I got you for the other eight.

837
01:07:41,280 --> 01:07:44,192
-How about a little air?
-Yes, I need some air.

838
01:07:46,080 --> 01:07:47,877
-That was totally weird.
-Totally harmless.

839
01:07:48,000 --> 01:07:50,673
lt was totally not harmless, by the way.

840
01:07:50,920 --> 01:07:52,114
We're dancing. No one's even watching.

841
01:07:52,240 --> 01:07:53,912
Everybody who I work with...
No, you know why?

842
01:07:54,040 --> 01:07:56,998
I think you lost objectivity. I think
they just... People... We just danced.

843
01:07:57,120 --> 01:08:00,351
No, it was not just a dance. You don't
understand because you're you.

844
01:08:00,480 --> 01:08:03,119
And everybody knows
exactly who you are

845
01:08:03,240 --> 01:08:06,277
and how you are with girls
and all of that, which is completely fine.

846
01:08:06,440 --> 01:08:08,670
But, you know, then me, you're my boss,

847
01:08:08,800 --> 01:08:10,711
-and I'm dancing with you.
-I don't think it was taken that way.

848
01:08:10,840 --> 01:08:13,479
Because it makes me look like
the one who's trying to...

849
01:08:13,600 --> 01:08:15,477
-I just think you're overstating it.
-You know, and we're here,

850
01:08:15,600 --> 01:08:19,070
and then I'm wearing this ridiculous

851
01:08:19,200 --> 01:08:21,794
dress, and then we were dancing
like that and...

852
01:08:35,240 --> 01:08:37,959
-I would like a drink, please.
-Got it, okay.

853
01:08:39,320 --> 01:08:42,118
-I would like a vodka martini, please.
-Okay.

854
01:08:42,240 --> 01:08:46,677
Very dry with olives, a lot of olives.
Like, at least three olives.

855
01:08:47,560 --> 01:08:50,438
Two vodka martinis, extra dry,
extra olives, extra fast.

856
01:08:50,560 --> 01:08:52,596
Make one of them dirty, will you?

857
01:08:57,080 --> 01:08:59,548
Wow. Tony Stark.

858
01:08:59,920 --> 01:09:02,115
-Oh, hey.
-Fancy seeing you here.

859
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:06,955
-Carrie.
-Christine.

860
01:09:07,080 --> 01:09:08,035
That's right.

861
01:09:08,160 --> 01:09:10,628
You have a lot of nerve
showing up here tonight.

862
01:09:10,760 --> 01:09:12,034
Can I at least get a reaction from you?

863
01:09:12,160 --> 01:09:14,469
Panic. I would say panic is my reaction.

864
01:09:14,600 --> 01:09:15,874
'Cause I was referring
to your company's

865
01:09:16,000 --> 01:09:17,228
involvement in this latest atrocity.

866
01:09:17,360 --> 01:09:19,999
Yeah. They just put my name on the
invitation. I don't know what to tell you.

867
01:09:20,120 --> 01:09:22,111
I actually almost bought it,
hook, line and sinker.

868
01:09:22,240 --> 01:09:24,470
I was out of town for a couple months,
in case you didn't hear.

869
01:09:24,600 --> 01:09:26,750
ls this what you call accountability?

870
01:09:26,880 --> 01:09:29,474
lt's a town called Gulmira. Heard of it?

871
01:09:40,560 --> 01:09:42,869
-When were these taken?
-Yesterday.

872
01:09:43,360 --> 01:09:45,271
-I didn't approve any shipment.
-Well, your company did.

873
01:09:45,400 --> 01:09:47,231
Well, I'm not my company.

874
01:09:48,320 --> 01:09:51,392
-Please, do you mind?
-Have you seen these pictures?

875
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:52,794
-What's going on in Gulmira?
-Tony, Tony.

876
01:09:52,920 --> 01:09:56,037
-You can't afford to be this naive.
-You know what? I was naive before,

877
01:09:56,160 --> 01:09:57,912
when they said,
"Here's the line. We don't cross it.

878
01:09:58,040 --> 01:09:59,314
"This is how we do business."

879
01:09:59,440 --> 01:10:02,432
lf we're double-dealing under the table...
Are we?

880
01:10:02,920 --> 01:10:04,911
Tony, your picture, please!

881
01:10:07,120 --> 01:10:10,430
Let's take a picture. Come on.
Picture time!

882
01:10:12,160 --> 01:10:15,118
Tony. Who do you think locked you out?

883
01:10:15,880 --> 01:10:18,952
I was the one who filed
the injunction against you.

884
01:10:21,360 --> 01:10:23,920
lt was the only way I could protect you.

885
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:27,389
No. No.

886
01:10:35,120 --> 01:10:39,238
<i>The 1 5-mile hike to the outskirts</i>
<i>of Gulmira can only be described</i>

887
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:42,830
<i>as a descent into hell,</i>
<i>into a modern day</i> Heart of Darkness.

888
01:10:43,040 --> 01:10:45,793
<i>Simple farmers and herders</i>
<i>from peaceful villages</i>

889
01:10:45,920 --> 01:10:47,558
<i>have been driven from their homes,</i>

890
01:10:47,680 --> 01:10:51,719
<i>displaced from their lands by warlords</i>
<i>emboldened by a new-found power.</i>

891
01:10:52,040 --> 01:10:54,918
<i>Villagers have been forced to take</i>
<i>shelter in whatever crude dwellings</i>

892
01:10:55,040 --> 01:10:57,634
<i>they can find in the ruins</i>
<i>of other villages,</i>

893
01:10:57,760 --> 01:11:01,435
<i>or here in the remnants</i>
<i>of an old Soviet smelting plant.</i>

894
01:11:06,040 --> 01:11:09,271
<i>Recent violence has been attributed</i>
<i>to a group of foreign fighters</i>

895
01:11:09,400 --> 01:11:11,960
<i>referred to by locals as the Ten Rings.</i>

896
01:11:12,240 --> 01:11:15,391
<i>As you can see, these men are</i>
<i>heavily armed and on a mission.</i>

897
01:11:15,520 --> 01:11:19,433
<i>A mission that could prove fatal</i>
<i>to anyone who stands in their way.</i>

898
01:11:19,680 --> 01:11:22,114
<i>With no political will</i>
<i>or international pressure,</i>

899
01:11:22,240 --> 01:11:24,515
<i>there's very little hope</i>
<i>for these refugees.</i>

900
01:11:24,640 --> 01:11:27,757
<i>Around me, a woman begging for news</i>
<i>on her husband,</i>

901
01:11:27,880 --> 01:11:29,552
<i>who was kidnapped by insurgents,</i>

902
01:11:29,680 --> 01:11:32,069
<i>either forced to join their militia...</i>

903
01:11:33,080 --> 01:11:35,548
<i>Desperate refugees clutch</i>
<i>yellowed photographs,</i>

904
01:11:35,680 --> 01:11:38,114
<i>holding them up to anyone</i>
<i>who will stop.</i>

905
01:11:38,240 --> 01:11:41,676
<i>A child's simple question,</i>
<i>"Where are my mother and father?"</i>

906
01:11:43,280 --> 01:11:45,555
<i>There's very little hope</i>
<i>for these refugees,</i>

907
01:11:45,680 --> 01:11:49,309
<i>refugees who can only wonder who,</i>
<i>if anyone, will help.</i>

908
01:13:18,520 --> 01:13:19,635
Hurry it up.

909
01:13:19,760 --> 01:13:20,875
Put the women in the trucks.

910
01:13:21,000 --> 01:13:21,955
Stack the weapons here.

911
01:13:22,080 --> 01:13:23,035
Clear all the houses.

912
01:13:23,160 --> 01:13:24,718
That one there.
Faster. Faster.

913
01:13:32,560 --> 01:13:33,515
Grab that dog.

914
01:13:36,360 --> 01:13:38,316
Put him with the others.

915
01:13:48,760 --> 01:13:50,034
What the hell is this?

916
01:14:01,240 --> 01:14:02,992
Shoot this dog.

917
01:14:03,200 --> 01:14:04,679
You're all incompetent.

918
01:14:07,920 --> 01:14:08,875
Turn your head.

919
01:15:12,920 --> 01:15:14,558
<i>He's all yours.</i>

920
01:16:10,840 --> 01:16:12,831
What the hell was that?
Were we cleared to go in there?

921
01:16:12,960 --> 01:16:15,474
No, they were using human shields.
We never got the green light.

922
01:16:15,600 --> 01:16:17,238
Put me through to State.
They're going to be all over this.

923
01:16:17,360 --> 01:16:18,349
Get those monitors up!

924
01:16:18,480 --> 01:16:19,708
We got a bogey!

925
01:16:19,840 --> 01:16:21,831
-Wasn't Air Force!
-We got the ClA on the line?

926
01:16:21,960 --> 01:16:23,791
l've got Langley on the line.
They want to know if it's us.

927
01:16:23,920 --> 01:16:25,478
No, it definitely is not us, sir!

928
01:16:25,600 --> 01:16:27,158
-lt wasn't Navy.
-Wasn't Marines.

929
01:16:27,280 --> 01:16:29,635
I need answers!
Can I please get eyes on target?

930
01:16:29,760 --> 01:16:31,876
-Negative, negative.
-Cannot identify.

931
01:16:32,000 --> 01:16:34,468
Get me Colonel Rhodes from
Weapons Development down here now!

932
01:16:41,040 --> 01:16:42,712
We ran an lD check
and cross-referenced

933
01:16:42,840 --> 01:16:44,432
with all known databases.
We have nothing.

934
01:16:44,560 --> 01:16:46,630
Any high altitude surveillance
in the region?

935
01:16:46,760 --> 01:16:48,352
We got an AWAC
and a Global Hawk in the area.

936
01:16:48,480 --> 01:16:50,038
So this thing just appeared
out of nowhere?

937
01:16:50,160 --> 01:16:51,388
How come it didn't show up
on the radar?

938
01:16:51,520 --> 01:16:53,397
Got a minimal radar cross-section, sir.

939
01:16:53,520 --> 01:16:55,556
-ls it stealth?
-No, sir, it's tiny.

940
01:16:55,720 --> 01:16:57,915
We think it's an unmanned
aerial vehicle.

941
01:16:58,040 --> 01:16:59,712
Colonel, what are we dealing with here?

942
01:17:02,200 --> 01:17:04,998
-Let me make a call.
-Sergeant, clear a hole.

943
01:17:08,440 --> 01:17:10,158
-Hello?
-Tony?

944
01:17:10,280 --> 01:17:11,872
<i>-Who's this?</i>
-lt's Rhodes.

945
01:17:12,200 --> 01:17:14,111
-Sorry, hello?
<i>-I said it's Rhodes.</i>

946
01:17:14,240 --> 01:17:16,993
-Speak up, please.
-What in the hell is that noise?

947
01:17:17,120 --> 01:17:20,351
-Oh, yeah, I'm driving with the top down.
-Yeah, well, I need your help right now.

948
01:17:20,480 --> 01:17:21,799
<i>lt's funny how that works, huh?</i>

949
01:17:21,920 --> 01:17:25,117
Yeah. Speaking of funny, we've got a
weapons depot that was just blown up

950
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:26,753
a few clicks from where
you were being held captive.

951
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:28,438
<i>Well, that's a hot spot.</i>

952
01:17:28,560 --> 01:17:30,915
<i>Sounds like someone stepped in</i>
<i>and did your job for you, huh?</i>

953
01:17:31,040 --> 01:17:32,029
Why do you sound out of breath, Tony?

954
01:17:32,160 --> 01:17:33,275
<i>I'm not, I was just jogging in the canyon.</i>

955
01:17:33,400 --> 01:17:35,072
-I thought you were driving.
<i>-Right, I was driving</i>

956
01:17:35,200 --> 01:17:36,838
<i>to the canyon, where I'm going to jog.</i>

957
01:17:36,960 --> 01:17:39,190
You sure you don't have any tech
in that area I should know about?

958
01:17:39,320 --> 01:17:40,673
<i>-Nope!</i>
-Bogey spotted!

959
01:17:40,800 --> 01:17:43,394
-Whiplash, come in hot.
-Okay, good, 'cause I'm staring at one

960
01:17:43,520 --> 01:17:46,751
right now, and it's about to be blown
to kingdom come.

961
01:17:47,440 --> 01:17:49,078
That's my exit.

962
01:17:53,680 --> 01:17:56,911
<i>Ballroom, this is Whiplash One.</i>
<i>l've got the bogey in my sights.</i>

963
01:17:57,160 --> 01:17:58,513
Whiplash One, what is it?

964
01:17:58,640 --> 01:17:59,868
<i>l've got no idea.</i>

965
01:18:00,000 --> 01:18:02,195
-You have radio contact?
<i>-Non responsive, sir.</i>

966
01:18:02,320 --> 01:18:03,275
Then you are clear to engage.

967
01:18:05,280 --> 01:18:06,235
<i>Hit it.</i>

968
01:18:10,880 --> 01:18:13,713
<i>That bogey just went supersonic.</i>
<i>I got a lock!</i>

969
01:18:17,600 --> 01:18:19,477
<i>-lnbound missile.</i>
-Flares!

970
01:18:22,440 --> 01:18:24,874
<i>Wait a second. Bogey deployed flares!</i>

971
01:18:38,640 --> 01:18:39,755
Deploy flaps!

972
01:18:40,960 --> 01:18:42,109
Holy!

973
01:18:42,240 --> 01:18:43,719
That thing just jumped off the radar, sir.

974
01:18:43,840 --> 01:18:45,273
The sat visual has been lost.

975
01:18:45,400 --> 01:18:46,958
<i>No way that's a UAV.</i>

976
01:18:47,080 --> 01:18:48,115
What is it?

977
01:18:48,240 --> 01:18:49,719
I can't see anything.

978
01:18:49,840 --> 01:18:52,149
<i>Whatever it was, it just bought the farm.</i>

979
01:18:52,680 --> 01:18:55,114
<i>I think bogey's been handled, sir.</i>

980
01:19:04,160 --> 01:19:05,752
-Hello?
<i>-Hi, Rhodey, it's me.</i>

981
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:07,438
-lt's who?
<i>-I'm sorry, it is me.</i>

982
01:19:07,560 --> 01:19:08,754
<i>You asked.</i>
<i>What you were asking about is me.</i>

983
01:19:08,880 --> 01:19:10,279
No, see, this isn't a game.

984
01:19:10,400 --> 01:19:13,517
You do not send civilian equipment
into my active war zone.

985
01:19:13,640 --> 01:19:15,437
-You understand that?
-This is not a piece of equipment.

986
01:19:15,560 --> 01:19:18,199
I'm in it. lt's a suit. lt's me!

987
01:19:18,320 --> 01:19:20,595
Rhodey, you got anything for me?

988
01:19:21,760 --> 01:19:24,991
<i>-Mark your position and return to base.</i>
<i>-Roger that, Ballroom.</i>

989
01:19:27,120 --> 01:19:28,189
<i>On your belly!</i>

990
01:19:28,320 --> 01:19:30,117
<i>lt looks like a man!</i>

991
01:19:30,320 --> 01:19:32,834
<i>Shake him off! Roll! Roll!</i>

992
01:19:40,600 --> 01:19:41,669
<i>I'm hit! I'm hit!</i>

993
01:19:41,800 --> 01:19:43,950
lt's confirmed. He has been hit.

994
01:19:47,960 --> 01:19:49,837
<i>Punch out! Punch out!</i>

995
01:19:56,040 --> 01:19:57,678
<i>Whiplash One down.</i>

996
01:19:57,800 --> 01:19:59,233
Whiplash Two, do you see a chute?

997
01:19:59,360 --> 01:20:01,476
<i>Negative! No chute, no chute!</i>

998
01:20:06,800 --> 01:20:08,119
<i>My chute's jammed!</i>

999
01:20:13,920 --> 01:20:16,150
<i>Sir, l've got a visual on the bogey.</i>

1000
01:20:16,280 --> 01:20:18,748
Whiplash Two, reengage.
lf you get a clear shot, you take it.

1001
01:20:21,200 --> 01:20:22,918
Major, we don't even know
what we're shooting at.

1002
01:20:23,040 --> 01:20:24,996
-Call off the Raptors.
-That thing just took out an F-22

1003
01:20:25,120 --> 01:20:26,394
inside a legal no fly zone!

1004
01:20:26,520 --> 01:20:28,670
Whiplash Two,
if you have a clear shot, take it!

1005
01:20:28,800 --> 01:20:31,075
<i>You've been reengaged.</i>
<i>Execute evasive manoeuvre.</i>

1006
01:20:31,200 --> 01:20:32,428
Keep going!

1007
01:20:39,760 --> 01:20:41,671
<i>Good chute! Good chute!</i>

1008
01:20:49,040 --> 01:20:51,713
-Tony, you still there?
<i>-Hey, thanks.</i>

1009
01:20:51,840 --> 01:20:54,274
Oh, my God, you crazy son of a bitch.

1010
01:20:55,120 --> 01:20:56,439
You owe me a plane.
You know that, right?

1011
01:20:58,160 --> 01:21:00,515
Yeah, well, technically, he hit me.

1012
01:21:00,640 --> 01:21:02,198
<i>Now are you going to come by</i>
<i>and see what I'm working on?</i>

1013
01:21:02,320 --> 01:21:04,993
No, no, no, no, no, no,
the less I know, the better.

1014
01:21:05,120 --> 01:21:06,599
Now, what am I supposed
to tell the press?

1015
01:21:06,720 --> 01:21:09,075
<i>Training exercise.</i>
<i>lsn't that the usual BS?</i>

1016
01:21:09,200 --> 01:21:10,713
<i>lt's not that simple.</i>

1017
01:21:11,600 --> 01:21:13,318
An unfortunate training exercise

1018
01:21:13,440 --> 01:21:16,193
involving an F-22 Raptor
occurred yesterday.

1019
01:21:16,920 --> 01:21:20,151
I am pleased to report
that the pilot was not injured.

1020
01:21:20,280 --> 01:21:23,989
<i>As for the unexpected turn of events</i>
<i>on the ground in Gulmira,</i>

1021
01:21:24,120 --> 01:21:27,430
<i>it is still unclear</i>
<i>who or what intervened,</i>

1022
01:21:27,560 --> 01:21:31,473
<i>but I can assure you that the United</i>
<i>States government was not involved.</i>

1023
01:21:33,480 --> 01:21:34,469
Hey!

1024
01:21:36,360 --> 01:21:38,112
<i>lt is a tight fit, sir.</i>

1025
01:21:39,120 --> 01:21:41,839
<i>Sir, the more you struggle,</i>
<i>the more this is going to hurt.</i>

1026
01:21:41,960 --> 01:21:43,757
Be gentle. This is my first time.

1027
01:21:44,680 --> 01:21:47,319
I designed this to come off, so... Hey.

1028
01:21:48,560 --> 01:21:52,109
-I really should be able to...
<i>-Please, try not to move, sir.</i>

1029
01:21:53,680 --> 01:21:55,830
What's going on here?

1030
01:22:00,240 --> 01:22:04,074
Let's face it. This is not the worst
thing you've caught me doing.

1031
01:22:04,640 --> 01:22:06,437
Are those bullet holes?

1032
01:22:32,800 --> 01:22:33,949
Welcome.

1033
01:22:37,200 --> 01:22:39,191
Compliments of Tony Stark.

1034
01:22:40,120 --> 01:22:43,590
lf you'd killed him when you were
supposed to, you'd still have a face.

1035
01:22:43,720 --> 01:22:45,676
You paid us trinkets to kill a prince.

1036
01:22:45,800 --> 01:22:47,438
Show me the weapon.

1037
01:22:48,680 --> 01:22:51,956
Come. Leave your guards outside.

1038
01:23:08,080 --> 01:23:10,469
His escape bore unexpected fruit.

1039
01:23:13,080 --> 01:23:14,911
So this is how he did it.

1040
01:23:15,280 --> 01:23:17,635
This is only a first, crude effort.

1041
01:23:17,880 --> 01:23:20,030
Stark has perfected his design.

1042
01:23:20,520 --> 01:23:22,875
He has made a masterpiece of death.

1043
01:23:23,560 --> 01:23:26,552
A man with a dozen of these
can rule all of Asia.

1044
01:23:28,120 --> 01:23:30,315
And you dream of Stark's throne.

1045
01:23:32,080 --> 01:23:34,196
We have a common enemy.

1046
01:23:38,360 --> 01:23:40,191
lf we are still in business,

1047
01:23:42,680 --> 01:23:44,750
I will give you these designs

1048
01:23:46,240 --> 01:23:47,195
as a gift.

1049
01:23:48,800 --> 01:23:50,119
And in turn,

1050
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:56,595
I hope you'll repay me with
a gift of iron soldiers.

1051
01:24:07,160 --> 01:24:09,958
This is the only gift you shall receive.

1052
01:24:12,880 --> 01:24:14,154
Technology.

1053
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:19,356
lt's always been your Achilles' heel
in this part of the world.

1054
01:24:20,560 --> 01:24:23,552
Don't worry. It'll only last for 15 minutes.

1055
01:24:24,720 --> 01:24:27,029
That's the least of your problems.

1056
01:24:32,080 --> 01:24:34,594
Crate up the armour and the rest of it.

1057
01:24:36,200 --> 01:24:38,111
All right, let's finish up here.

1058
01:24:41,920 --> 01:24:44,718
Set up Sector 16
underneath the arc reactor,

1059
01:24:44,840 --> 01:24:48,196
and I'm going to want this data masked.
Recruit our top engineers.

1060
01:24:48,320 --> 01:24:50,072
I want a prototype right away.

1061
01:24:57,960 --> 01:25:00,952
Hey. You busy?
You mind if I send you on an errand?

1062
01:25:01,080 --> 01:25:03,150
I need you to go to my office.

1063
01:25:03,680 --> 01:25:06,035
You're going to hack into the mainframe
and you're going to retrieve all

1064
01:25:06,160 --> 01:25:08,549
the recent shipping manifests.
This is a lock chip.

1065
01:25:08,680 --> 01:25:10,159
This'll get you in.

1066
01:25:10,280 --> 01:25:11,759
lt's probably under Executive Files.

1067
01:25:11,880 --> 01:25:14,110
lf not, they put it on a ghost drive,
in which case you need

1068
01:25:14,240 --> 01:25:16,800
to look for the lowest numeric heading.

1069
01:25:17,080 --> 01:25:19,469
And what do you plan to do with
this information if I bring it back here?

1070
01:25:19,600 --> 01:25:20,555
Same drill.

1071
01:25:20,680 --> 01:25:22,636
They've been dealing under the table,
and I'm going to stop them.

1072
01:25:22,760 --> 01:25:25,672
I'm going to find my weapons
and destroy them.

1073
01:25:26,520 --> 01:25:27,509
Tony,

1074
01:25:29,760 --> 01:25:31,512
you know that
I would help you with anything,

1075
01:25:31,640 --> 01:25:35,428
but I cannot help you if
you're going to start all of this again.

1076
01:25:35,560 --> 01:25:38,950
There is nothing except this.
There's no art opening.

1077
01:25:39,240 --> 01:25:42,277
There is no benefit.
There is nothing to sign.

1078
01:25:43,400 --> 01:25:46,312
There is the next mission
and nothing else.

1079
01:25:47,520 --> 01:25:48,794
ls that so?

1080
01:25:50,920 --> 01:25:52,319
Well, then, I quit.

1081
01:25:55,280 --> 01:25:56,793
You stood by my side all these years

1082
01:25:56,920 --> 01:25:59,593
while I reaped
the benefits of destruction.

1083
01:25:59,920 --> 01:26:01,672
And now that I'm trying
to protect the people

1084
01:26:01,800 --> 01:26:03,518
that I put in harm's way,
you're going to walk out?

1085
01:26:03,640 --> 01:26:07,838
You're going to kill yourself, Tony.
I'm not going to be a part of it.

1086
01:26:07,960 --> 01:26:09,837
I shouldn't be alive,

1087
01:26:11,120 --> 01:26:13,111
unless it was for a reason.

1088
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:15,712
I'm not crazy, Pepper.

1089
01:26:16,240 --> 01:26:19,232
I just finally know what I have to do.

1090
01:26:23,440 --> 01:26:26,079
And I know in my heart that it's right.

1091
01:26:41,200 --> 01:26:43,509
You're all I have, too, you know.

1092
01:27:50,240 --> 01:27:54,791
Sector 16?
What are you up to, Obadiah?

1093
01:28:07,240 --> 01:28:11,358
<i>You did not tell us that the target you</i>
<i>paid us to kill was the great Tony Stark.</i>

1094
01:28:11,480 --> 01:28:12,913
<i>-As you can see, Obadiah Stane...</i>
-Oh, my God.

1095
01:28:13,040 --> 01:28:15,600
<i>...your deception and lies</i>
<i>will cost you dearly.</i>

1096
01:28:15,720 --> 01:28:18,280
<i>The price to kill Tony Stark</i>
<i>has just gone up.</i>

1097
01:28:22,160 --> 01:28:26,312
So, what are we going to do about this?

1098
01:28:37,880 --> 01:28:40,997
I know what you're going through,
Pepper.

1099
01:28:48,440 --> 01:28:51,910
Tony. He always gets the good stuff,
doesn't he?

1100
01:29:12,720 --> 01:29:16,872
I was so happy when he came home.

1101
01:29:17,000 --> 01:29:19,639
lt was like we got him back
from the dead.

1102
01:29:22,600 --> 01:29:24,431
Now I realise,

1103
01:29:26,680 --> 01:29:29,797
well, Tony never really did
come home, did he?

1104
01:29:31,480 --> 01:29:34,040
He left a part of himself in that cave.

1105
01:29:36,720 --> 01:29:38,233
Breaks my heart.

1106
01:29:40,480 --> 01:29:44,234
Well, he's a complicated person.

1107
01:29:46,880 --> 01:29:50,111
He's been through a lot.
I think he'll be all right.

1108
01:29:56,200 --> 01:29:58,794
You are a very rare woman.

1109
01:30:01,240 --> 01:30:03,276
Tony doesn't know how lucky he is.

1110
01:30:05,960 --> 01:30:07,837
Thank you. Thanks.

1111
01:30:09,800 --> 01:30:11,711
I'd better get back there.

1112
01:30:17,000 --> 01:30:18,911
ls that today's paper?

1113
01:30:20,520 --> 01:30:21,475
Yes.

1114
01:30:22,280 --> 01:30:23,554
Do you mind?

1115
01:30:24,200 --> 01:30:25,918
-Not at all.
-Puzzle.

1116
01:30:26,040 --> 01:30:27,234
Of course.

1117
01:30:30,640 --> 01:30:31,868
Take care.

1118
01:30:55,080 --> 01:30:57,799
Ms Potts? We had an appointment.
Did you forget about our appointment?

1119
01:30:57,920 --> 01:30:59,353
Nope, right now. Come with me.

1120
01:30:59,480 --> 01:31:00,515
-Right now?
-We're going to have it right now.

1121
01:31:00,640 --> 01:31:02,278
-Yeah, walk with me.
-Okay.

1122
01:31:03,440 --> 01:31:05,476
I'm going to give you the meeting
of your life. Your office.

1123
01:31:07,040 --> 01:31:09,713
Yeah, we've been working
our best to do it.

1124
01:31:10,120 --> 01:31:13,476
Absolutely, we're...
I'm going to have to call you back.

1125
01:31:13,680 --> 01:31:16,240
Mr Stane?
Sir, we've explored

1126
01:31:16,360 --> 01:31:18,555
what you've asked us, and it seems
as though there's a little hiccup.

1127
01:31:18,680 --> 01:31:20,193
-Actually...
-A hiccup?

1128
01:31:20,320 --> 01:31:23,915
Yes, to power the suit, sir,
the technology actually doesn't exist.

1129
01:31:24,160 --> 01:31:27,152
-So it's...
-Wait, wait, wait. The technology?

1130
01:31:27,280 --> 01:31:32,957
William, here is the technology.
l've asked you to simply make it smaller.

1131
01:31:33,080 --> 01:31:36,868
Okay, sir, and that's what we're trying
to do, but honestly, it's impossible.

1132
01:31:37,000 --> 01:31:43,269
Tony Stark was able to build this
in a cave! With a box of scraps!

1133
01:31:45,440 --> 01:31:48,318
Well, I'm sorry. I'm not Tony Stark.

1134
01:32:03,840 --> 01:32:04,829
<i>Tony?</i>

1135
01:32:07,400 --> 01:32:10,551
<i>Tony, are you there? Hello?</i>

1136
01:32:12,080 --> 01:32:13,229
Breathe.

1137
01:32:14,400 --> 01:32:16,960
Easy, easy.

1138
01:32:19,000 --> 01:32:21,150
You remember this one, right?

1139
01:32:22,840 --> 01:32:25,035
lt's a shame the government
didn't approve it.

1140
01:32:25,160 --> 01:32:29,073
There's so many applications
for causing short-term paralysis.

1141
01:32:31,360 --> 01:32:32,509
Tony.

1142
01:32:34,760 --> 01:32:38,912
When I ordered the hit on you,

1143
01:32:41,480 --> 01:32:43,835
I worried that I was

1144
01:32:46,760 --> 01:32:48,671
killing the golden goose.

1145
01:32:50,000 --> 01:32:53,595
But, you see, it was just

1146
01:32:54,920 --> 01:32:57,036
fate that you survived that.

1147
01:33:01,960 --> 01:33:05,589
You had one last golden egg to give.

1148
01:33:09,640 --> 01:33:14,714
Do you really think that just because
you have an idea, it belongs to you?

1149
01:33:18,480 --> 01:33:23,349
Your father, he helped give us
the atomic bomb.

1150
01:33:23,480 --> 01:33:27,519
Now, what kind of world would it be
today if he was as selfish as you?

1151
01:33:37,160 --> 01:33:38,718
Oh, it's beautiful.

1152
01:33:41,240 --> 01:33:45,836
Tony, this is your Ninth Symphony.

1153
01:33:48,080 --> 01:33:50,389
What a masterpiece. Look at that.

1154
01:33:51,760 --> 01:33:53,432
This is your legacy.

1155
01:33:55,880 --> 01:34:00,829
A new generation of weapons
with this at its heart.

1156
01:34:03,960 --> 01:34:07,509
Weapons that will help steer the world
back on course,

1157
01:34:07,640 --> 01:34:09,756
put the balance of power in our hands.

1158
01:34:11,280 --> 01:34:12,793
The right hands.

1159
01:34:15,840 --> 01:34:20,152
I wish you could see my prototype.

1160
01:34:21,560 --> 01:34:22,959
lt's not as...

1161
01:34:24,280 --> 01:34:27,113
Well, not as conservative as yours.

1162
01:34:29,120 --> 01:34:31,793
Too bad you had to involve Pepper
in this.

1163
01:34:32,240 --> 01:34:34,674
I would have preferred that she lived.

1164
01:34:47,200 --> 01:34:49,395
What do you mean,
he paid to have Tony killed?

1165
01:34:49,520 --> 01:34:51,954
Pepper, slow down.
Why would Obadiah...

1166
01:34:53,200 --> 01:34:54,394
Okay, where's Tony now?

1167
01:34:54,520 --> 01:34:56,112
I don't know.
He's not answering his phone.

1168
01:34:56,240 --> 01:34:58,276
Please go over there
and make sure everything's okay.

1169
01:34:58,400 --> 01:35:00,834
Thank you, Rhodey. I know a shortcut.

1170
01:36:04,480 --> 01:36:05,708
Good boy.

1171
01:36:43,920 --> 01:36:44,909
Tony?

1172
01:36:47,520 --> 01:36:48,509
Tony?

1173
01:36:50,240 --> 01:36:51,275
Tony?

1174
01:36:53,360 --> 01:36:54,395
Tony?

1175
01:36:57,000 --> 01:36:57,989
Tony!

1176
01:37:00,160 --> 01:37:02,310
Tony! You okay?

1177
01:37:02,680 --> 01:37:06,150
-Where's Pepper?
-She's fine. She's with five agents.

1178
01:37:06,280 --> 01:37:08,430
They're about to arrest Obadiah.

1179
01:37:08,600 --> 01:37:10,591
That's not going to be enough.

1180
01:37:33,480 --> 01:37:39,191
Section 16. Section 16. There it is.

1181
01:37:47,880 --> 01:37:50,440
My key's not working.
lt's not opening the door.

1182
01:37:50,560 --> 01:37:52,551
Oh, wow! What's that?
lt's, like, a little device?

1183
01:37:52,680 --> 01:37:53,999
lt's, like, a thing that's going
to pick the lock?

1184
01:37:54,120 --> 01:37:56,714
You might want to take
a few steps back.

1185
01:38:14,560 --> 01:38:16,949
That's the coolest thing l've ever seen.

1186
01:38:17,080 --> 01:38:19,719
Not bad, huh? Let's do it.

1187
01:38:26,160 --> 01:38:28,390
You need me to do anything else?

1188
01:38:29,000 --> 01:38:30,672
<i>Keep the skies clear.</i>

1189
01:38:35,640 --> 01:38:36,834
Damn!

1190
01:38:44,600 --> 01:38:46,158
Next time, baby.

1191
01:39:15,080 --> 01:39:18,277
Looks like you were right.
He was building a suit.

1192
01:39:18,880 --> 01:39:20,757
I thought it'd be bigger.

1193
01:40:03,800 --> 01:40:04,755
Take him out!

1194
01:40:15,200 --> 01:40:17,077
How do you think the Mark l
chest piece is going to hold up?

1195
01:40:17,200 --> 01:40:19,395
<i>The suit's at 48% power and falling, sir.</i>

1196
01:40:19,520 --> 01:40:22,034
<i>That chest piece</i>
<i>was never designed for sustained flight.</i>

1197
01:40:22,160 --> 01:40:23,559
Keep me posted.

1198
01:40:25,320 --> 01:40:26,275
<i>Pepper!</i>

1199
01:40:26,400 --> 01:40:29,198
-Tony! Tony, are you okay?
<i>-I'm fine. How are...</i>

1200
01:40:29,360 --> 01:40:31,112
-Obadiah, he's gone insane!
<i>-I know.</i>

1201
01:40:31,240 --> 01:40:32,912
<i>-Listen, you'd better get out of there.</i>
-He built a suit.

1202
01:40:33,040 --> 01:40:34,393
<i>Get out of there right now!</i>

1203
01:40:45,800 --> 01:40:47,995
<i>Where do you think you're going?</i>

1204
01:40:53,320 --> 01:40:56,153
<i>Your services are no longer required.</i>

1205
01:40:56,400 --> 01:40:57,753
<i>Stane!</i>

1206
01:41:21,960 --> 01:41:23,552
<i>I love this suit!</i>

1207
01:41:23,680 --> 01:41:26,717
<i>-Put them down!</i>
<i>-Collateral damage, Tony.</i>

1208
01:41:28,240 --> 01:41:30,151
Divert power to chest RT.

1209
01:41:38,560 --> 01:41:40,551
<i>Power reduced to 19%.</i>

1210
01:41:48,120 --> 01:41:49,155
<i>Lady!</i>

1211
01:41:51,000 --> 01:41:52,911
<i>No, no, no, no, no, no!</i>

1212
01:42:14,120 --> 01:42:16,918
<i>For 30 years, l've been holding you up!</i>

1213
01:42:21,240 --> 01:42:23,549
<i>I built this company from nothing!</i>

1214
01:42:25,760 --> 01:42:28,194
<i>Nothing is going to stand in my way.</i>

1215
01:42:34,200 --> 01:42:36,509
<i>Least of all you!</i>

1216
01:42:45,680 --> 01:42:48,797
<i>lmpressive!</i>
<i>You've upgraded your armour!</i>

1217
01:42:49,360 --> 01:42:51,954
<i>l've made some upgrades of my own!</i>

1218
01:43:00,000 --> 01:43:01,831
<i>Sir, it appears that his suit can fly.</i>

1219
01:43:01,960 --> 01:43:03,552
Duly noted.
Take me to maximum altitude.

1220
01:43:03,680 --> 01:43:05,796
<i>With only 1 5% power,</i>
<i>the odds of reaching that...</i>

1221
01:43:05,920 --> 01:43:07,956
I know the math! Do it!

1222
01:43:15,920 --> 01:43:18,115
Sir, you're not going to believe this.
That thing is back.

1223
01:43:18,240 --> 01:43:20,708
Get me Major Allen. Scramble the jets!

1224
01:43:23,360 --> 01:43:26,193
Not necessary, people.
Just a training exercise.

1225
01:43:26,320 --> 01:43:27,469
Yes, sir.

1226
01:43:35,120 --> 01:43:36,951
<i>-Thirteen percent power, sir.</i>
-Climb!

1227
01:43:40,840 --> 01:43:42,751
<i>-Eleven percent.</i>
-Keep going!

1228
01:43:49,240 --> 01:43:51,231
<i>-Seven percent power.</i>
-Just leave it on the screen!

1229
01:43:51,360 --> 01:43:52,839
Stop telling me!

1230
01:44:02,160 --> 01:44:06,551
<i>You had a great idea, Tony, but my</i>
<i>suit is more advanced in every way!</i>

1231
01:44:07,120 --> 01:44:09,076
<i>How'd you solve the icing problem?</i>

1232
01:44:09,200 --> 01:44:10,599
lcing problem?

1233
01:44:12,720 --> 01:44:14,950
<i>Might want to look into it.</i>

1234
01:44:26,200 --> 01:44:27,394
<i>Two percent.</i>

1235
01:44:29,520 --> 01:44:32,239
<i>We are now running</i>
<i>on emergency backup power.</i>

1236
01:44:43,440 --> 01:44:46,716
-Potts!
-Tony! Oh, my God, are you okay?

1237
01:44:46,840 --> 01:44:50,753
I'm almost out of power. l've got to get
out of this thing. I'll be right there.

1238
01:44:50,880 --> 01:44:52,199
<i>Nice try!</i>

1239
01:45:04,280 --> 01:45:08,273
-Weapons status?
<i>-Repulsors offline. Missiles offline.</i>

1240
01:45:12,320 --> 01:45:13,799
Flares!

1241
01:45:22,000 --> 01:45:23,911
<i>Very clever, Tony.</i>

1242
01:45:29,040 --> 01:45:31,395
-Potts?
-Tony!

1243
01:45:31,520 --> 01:45:32,475
This isn't working.

1244
01:45:32,600 --> 01:45:34,716
We're going to have to overload
the reactor and blast the roof.

1245
01:45:34,840 --> 01:45:37,559
-Well, how are you going to do that?
-You're going to do it.

1246
01:45:37,680 --> 01:45:39,989
Go to the central console,
open up all the circuits.

1247
01:45:40,120 --> 01:45:41,439
When I get clear of the roof,
I'll let you know.

1248
01:45:41,560 --> 01:45:43,994
You're going to hit
the master bypass button.

1249
01:45:44,120 --> 01:45:45,394
lt's going to fry everything up here.

1250
01:45:47,520 --> 01:45:49,670
Okay. I'm going in now.

1251
01:45:49,800 --> 01:45:52,872
Make sure you wait till I clear the roof.
I'll buy you some time.

1252
01:46:02,040 --> 01:46:03,712
<i>This looks important!</i>

1253
01:46:23,800 --> 01:46:26,439
I never had a taste for this sort of thing,

1254
01:46:26,560 --> 01:46:30,473
but I must admit,
I'm deeply enjoying the suit!

1255
01:46:38,440 --> 01:46:40,795
You finally outdid yourself, Tony!

1256
01:46:43,080 --> 01:46:45,116
You'd have made your father proud!

1257
01:46:49,920 --> 01:46:52,275
lt's ready, Tony! Get off the roof!

1258
01:47:11,040 --> 01:47:12,268
Tony!

1259
01:47:13,480 --> 01:47:14,993
How ironic, Tony!

1260
01:47:16,760 --> 01:47:21,436
Trying to rid the world of weapons,
you gave it its best one ever!

1261
01:47:21,680 --> 01:47:27,312
-Pepper!
-And now I'm going to kill you with it!

1262
01:47:30,280 --> 01:47:33,909
-You ripped out my targeting system!
-Time to hit the button!

1263
01:47:34,040 --> 01:47:37,828
-You told me not to!
-Hold still, you little prick!

1264
01:47:39,840 --> 01:47:42,229
-Just do it!
-You'll die!

1265
01:47:45,280 --> 01:47:46,679
Push it!

1266
01:48:41,920 --> 01:48:43,592
Tony!

1267
01:48:51,760 --> 01:48:53,716
<i>You've all received the official</i>
<i>statement of what occurred</i>

1268
01:48:53,840 --> 01:48:55,990
<i>at Stark lndustries last night.</i>

1269
01:48:56,360 --> 01:49:00,638
<i>There have been unconfirmed reports</i>
<i>that a robotic prototype malfunctioned</i>

1270
01:49:00,800 --> 01:49:03,234
<i>and caused damage to the arc reactor.</i>

1271
01:49:04,000 --> 01:49:06,116
<i>Fortunately, a member</i>
<i>of Tony Stark's personal security staff...</i>

1272
01:49:06,240 --> 01:49:08,071
"lron Man." That's kind of catchy.
lt's got a nice ring to it.

1273
01:49:08,200 --> 01:49:11,636
I mean, it's not technically accurate.
The suit's a gold-titanium alloy,

1274
01:49:11,760 --> 01:49:14,228
but it's kind of evocative,
the imagery, anyway.

1275
01:49:14,360 --> 01:49:15,873
Here's your alibi.

1276
01:49:16,760 --> 01:49:17,749
Okay.

1277
01:49:17,880 --> 01:49:19,916
-You were on your yacht.
-Yeah.

1278
01:49:20,040 --> 01:49:22,031
We have port papers that put you
in Avalon all night,

1279
01:49:22,160 --> 01:49:23,752
and sworn statements
from 50 of your guests.

1280
01:49:23,880 --> 01:49:26,838
See, I was thinking maybe we should
say it was just Pepper and me

1281
01:49:26,960 --> 01:49:28,632
alone on the island.

1282
01:49:29,920 --> 01:49:31,114
-That's what happened.
-All right.

1283
01:49:31,240 --> 01:49:33,231
Just read it, word for word.

1284
01:49:35,080 --> 01:49:36,991
There's nothing about Stane here.

1285
01:49:37,120 --> 01:49:39,759
That's being handled. He's on vacation.

1286
01:49:40,640 --> 01:49:42,949
Small aircraft have
such a poor safety record.

1287
01:49:43,080 --> 01:49:45,435
But what about the whole cover story
that it's a bodyguard?

1288
01:49:45,560 --> 01:49:48,313
He's my... I mean, is that...
That's kind of flimsy, don't you think?

1289
01:49:48,440 --> 01:49:50,590
This isn't my first rodeo, Mr Stark.

1290
01:49:50,720 --> 01:49:54,508
Just stick to the official statement,
and soon, this will all be behind you.

1291
01:49:54,640 --> 01:49:56,756
You've got 90 seconds.

1292
01:49:59,560 --> 01:50:01,118
Agent Coulson?

1293
01:50:01,800 --> 01:50:06,078
I just wanted to say thank you very much
for all of your help.

1294
01:50:06,200 --> 01:50:08,953
That's what we do.
You'll be hearing from us.

1295
01:50:09,240 --> 01:50:12,437
-From the Strategic Homeland...
-Just call us S.H.l.E.L.D.

1296
01:50:12,800 --> 01:50:13,869
Right.

1297
01:50:14,840 --> 01:50:18,549
-Let's get this show on the road.
-You know, it's actually not that bad.

1298
01:50:18,680 --> 01:50:20,796
Even I don't think I'm lron Man.

1299
01:50:20,960 --> 01:50:22,393
-You're not lron Man.
-Am so.

1300
01:50:22,520 --> 01:50:24,829
-You're not.
-All right, suit yourself.

1301
01:50:24,960 --> 01:50:28,748
You know, if I were lron Man, I'd have
this girlfriend who knew my true identity.

1302
01:50:28,880 --> 01:50:31,394
She'd be a wreck, 'cause she'd always
be worrying that I was going to die,

1303
01:50:31,520 --> 01:50:33,636
yet so proud of the man I'd become.

1304
01:50:33,760 --> 01:50:37,275
She'd be wildly conflicted,
which would only make her more

1305
01:50:38,960 --> 01:50:39,949
crazy about me.

1306
01:50:40,080 --> 01:50:41,638
Tell me you never think about that night.

1307
01:50:41,760 --> 01:50:43,512
-What night?
-You know.

1308
01:50:46,360 --> 01:50:51,832
Are you talking about the night that
we danced and went up on the roof,

1309
01:50:53,480 --> 01:50:58,793
and then you went downstairs
to get me a drink,

1310
01:50:58,920 --> 01:51:01,992
and you left me there, by myself?

1311
01:51:03,200 --> 01:51:05,589
ls that the night you're talking about?

1312
01:51:07,720 --> 01:51:08,709
Thought so.

1313
01:51:11,360 --> 01:51:14,909
-Will that be all, Mr Stark?
-Yes, that will be all, Miss Potts.

1314
01:51:15,040 --> 01:51:18,396
<i>And now, Mr Stark has</i>
<i>prepared a statement.</i>

1315
01:51:18,520 --> 01:51:21,398
<i>He will not be taking any questions.</i>
<i>Thank you.</i>

1316
01:51:25,440 --> 01:51:30,275
<i>Been a while since I was in front of you.</i>
<i>I figure I'll stick to the cards this time.</i>

1317
01:51:32,240 --> 01:51:35,118
<i>There's been speculation that I was</i>
<i>involved in the events that occurred</i>

1318
01:51:35,240 --> 01:51:36,434
<i>on the freeway and the rooftop...</i>

1319
01:51:36,560 --> 01:51:39,199
I'm sorry, Mr Stark, but do you
honestly expect us to believe that

1320
01:51:39,320 --> 01:51:42,869
that was a bodyguard
in a suit that conveniently appeared,

1321
01:51:43,000 --> 01:51:45,958
-despite the fact that you...
<i>-I know that it's confusing.</i>

1322
01:51:46,080 --> 01:51:49,470
<i>lt is one thing to question the official</i>
<i>story, and another thing entirely</i>

1323
01:51:49,600 --> 01:51:52,672
<i>to make wild accusations,</i>
<i>or insinuate that I'm a superhero.</i>

1324
01:51:52,800 --> 01:51:54,313
I never said you were a superhero.

1325
01:51:54,440 --> 01:51:59,514
<i>Didn't? Well, good, because that would</i>
<i>be outlandish and fantastic.</i>

1326
01:52:01,480 --> 01:52:04,552
<i>I'm just not the hero type. Clearly.</i>

1327
01:52:05,120 --> 01:52:07,918
<i>With this laundry list</i>
<i>of character defects,</i>

1328
01:52:08,040 --> 01:52:09,393
<i>all the mistakes l've made,</i>

1329
01:52:09,520 --> 01:52:12,671
<i>-largely public.</i>
-Just stick to the cards, man.

1330
01:52:12,800 --> 01:52:14,358
Yeah, okay. Yeah.

1331
01:52:16,400 --> 01:52:17,833
<i>The truth is</i>

1332
01:52:23,800 --> 01:52:25,199
<i>I am lron Man.</i>

1333
02:00:08,680 --> 02:00:09,829
Jarvis!

1334
02:00:09,960 --> 02:00:11,552
<i>Welcome home, sir.</i>

1335
02:00:14,920 --> 02:00:20,153
"I am lron Man." You think you're
the only superhero in the world?

1336
02:00:20,520 --> 02:00:23,592
Mr Stark, you've become part
of a bigger universe.

1337
02:00:23,720 --> 02:00:25,392
You just don't know it yet.

1338
02:00:25,920 --> 02:00:27,558
Who the hell are you?

1339
02:00:27,840 --> 02:00:30,400
Nick Fury, Director of S.H.I.E.L.D.

1340
02:00:32,440 --> 02:00:35,238
I'm here to talk to you
about the Avenger lnitiative.